.5$ disk scale\nlengths, regardless of the central surface density. The other expression can\nunderestimate the rotational speed by up to 12.5% at one scale length, though\nrather less so at larger radii.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 Aug 2018 23:05:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 30 Oct 2018 15:29:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 1 Nov 2018 18:16:42 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 5 Dec 2018 01:47:27 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 20 Jan 2019 18:26:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-01-23"}
